[220.385926, "i", "cat > BUGFIX_SUMMARY.txt << 'EOF'\nCHECKPOINT/RESUME BUG FIXES\n============================\n\nOriginal Issues:\n1. Checkpoint saved batch_num (number of batches) but used it as line number\n   - When batch_num=1, it only skipped 1 line instead of 1000 lines\n   - This caused almost all data to be reprocessed on resume\n\n2. INSERT OR REPLACE overwrote existing aggregates instead of accumulating\n   - On resume, previous batch results were lost/replaced\n   - This caused data loss for categories already processed\n\n3. Checkpoint file not properly flushed to disk\n   - Used open() without context manager\n   - No explicit flush() or fsync() calls\n   - Could result in empty/corrupt checkpoint on crash\n\nFixes Applied:\n1. Changed checkpoint to save actual line number (start_from + lines_processed)\n   - Now correctly skips all previously processed lines\n   - Added lines_processed counter to track position\n\n2. Changed to INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE\n   - Accumulates total_value and count instead of replacing\n   - Preserves "]
[220.38596, "i", "previous batch results when resuming\n\n3. Added proper file handling for checkpoint\n   - Used context manager (with statement)\n   - Added explicit f.flush() and os.fsync()\n   - Ensures checkpoint is written to disk before continuing\n\n4. Added conn.commit() after each batch\n   - Ensures database changes persist if process is killed\n\nVerification:\n- Interrupted run at 6000 records, resumed successfully\n- Final totals match clean run: 50000 records, 2494808.87 value\n- No data duplication or loss\nEOF\n"]
